{{Infobox person |name = Irving Abella |image = |alt = |caption = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1940|7|2}} |birth_place = [[Toronto|Toronto, Ontario]], Canada |birth_name = Irving Martin Abella |death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> |death_place = |spouse = [[Rosalie Abella]] |other_names = |known_for = |occupation = Writer, historian and academic |nationality = |awards = [[Order of Canada]] }} '''Irving Martin Abella''', {{Post-nominals|country=CAN|CM|OOnt|FRSC}} (born July 2, 1940) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] writer, historian and academic.
He specializes in the [[history of the Jews in Canada]] and the [[Labour movement|Canadian labour movement]].
==Biography== Born in [[Toronto|Toronto, Ontario]], he received his [[Bachelor of Arts]] degree (1963), [[Master of Arts]] (1964) degree, and [[Ph.D.]] (1969) from the [[University of Toronto]].
His books have included ''Coat of Many Colours: Two Centuries of Jewish Life in Canada'' (1990) and ''[[None is Too Many: Canada and the Jews of Europe 1933-1948]]'' (1982). He is a professor at [[York University]] and is a former president of the [[Canadian Jewish Congress]] (1992 to 1995).
In 1993, he was made a Member of the [[Order of Canada]]<ref>{{ cite web | url =http://archive.gg.ca/honours/search-recherche/honours-desc.asp?lang=e&TypeID=orc&id=1284 | title = Order of Canada | publisher=archive.gg.ca |date=2009-04-30 |accessdate=September 26, 2013 }}</ref> and a Fellow of the [[Royal Society of Canada]]. He was awarded the [[Queen Elizabeth II Golden Jubilee Medal]] in 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gg.ca/honours.aspx?q=&t=6&p=ON&c=&pg=1&Province=ON&types=6&advgjmRegion=Canada|title=Golden Jubilee Medal | publisher=www.gg.ca | accessdate=September 26, 2013 }}</ref> In 2014, he was made a Member of the [[Order of Ontario]] "for his contribution to documenting the story of Jewish Canadians, and his commitment to the principles of social justice and tolerance.".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.ontario.ca/mci/en/2014/01/new-appointees-to-the-order-of-ontario.html|title=New Appointees to the Order of Ontario|date=January 23, 2014}}</ref>
He is married to Canadian jurist [[Rosalie Abella|Rosalie Silberman Abella]], who was appointed to the [[Supreme Court of Canada]] in August, 2004. They have two sons, Jacob and Zachary. Irving Abella is the cousin of [[Isaac Abella]].
